---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Fractals in Nature - Unfold">

  <div class="fractal-container">

    <!-- Intro -->
    <section class="fractal-intro">
      <div class="intro-content">
        <h1>Fractals in Nature</h1>
        <p class="intro-text">
          A simple rule, repeated - and the universe builds itself.
        </p>
        <div class="scroll-hint">
          <span>↓</span>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Text 1: What is a fractal? -->
    <section class="fractal-text">
      <div class="text-content">
        <p>Look closely at a fern. Each leaf is a smaller copy of the whole frond. Zoom into that leaf, and each leaflet repeats the same shape again. This is self-similarity - the signature of a fractal.</p>
        <p class="faded">Nature doesn't design from blueprints. It gives a simple instruction, repeats it at every scale, and lets complexity emerge.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Viz 1: Fern -->
    <section class="fractal-section" data-viz="fern">
      <canvas></canvas>
      <div class="fractal-info">
        <h2>Barnsley Fern</h2>
        <p>Four affine transformations, chosen at random with weighted probabilities. Each point is born from the previous one - and yet a perfect fern appears. The algorithm of every frond that ever unfurled.</p>
        <span class="fractal-interact">move the mouse to stir the wind</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Text 2: From ferns to vegetables -->
    <section class="fractal-text">
      <div class="text-content">
        <p>The same principle that shapes a fern also sculpts one of the most extraordinary vegetables on Earth. The romanesco arranges its buds in Fibonacci spirals, and each bud is a perfect miniature of the whole.</p>
        <p class="faded">Fractals you can eat.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Viz 2: Romanesco -->
    <section class="fractal-section" data-viz="romanesco">
      <canvas></canvas>
      <div class="fractal-info">
        <h2>Romanesco</h2>
        <p>Golden angle phyllotaxis - 137.508° - distributes each floret without overlap. Each one is a recursive copy of the whole, spirals within spirals, down to the smallest bud.</p>
        <span class="fractal-interact">move the mouse to shift the light</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Text 3: From growth to discharge -->
    <section class="fractal-text">
      <div class="text-content">
        <p>Fractals don't only grow slowly. Sometimes they explode into existence - in milliseconds. When lightning searches for the path of least resistance, it branches recursively through the atmosphere.</p>
        <p class="faded">Each fork is a smaller version of the main bolt.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Viz 3: Lightning -->
    <section class="fractal-section" data-viz="lightning">
      <canvas></canvas>
      <div class="fractal-info">
        <h2>Lightning</h2>
        <p>Recursive branching through the atmosphere. The main channel forks, and each fork forks again - probability decreasing, thickness thinning, until the charge dissipates into the finest filaments.</p>
        <span class="fractal-interact">click to summon a bolt</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Text 4: From chaos to geometry -->
    <section class="fractal-text">
      <div class="text-content">
        <p>Some fractals are born from pure geometry. Take a triangle. Replace each edge with a smaller triangle. Repeat forever. The Koch snowflake has infinite perimeter trapped inside a finite area.</p>
        <p class="faded">A paradox that mirrors the crystalline symmetry of real snowflakes.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Viz 4: Koch Snowflake -->
    <section class="fractal-section" data-viz="koch">
      <canvas></canvas>
      <div class="fractal-info">
        <h2>Koch Snowflake</h2>
        <p>Start with a triangle. Subdivide each edge into four. Repeat six times. The perimeter grows toward infinity while the area barely changes - geometry at the edge of reason.</p>
        <span class="fractal-interact">hover to illuminate the edges</span>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Text 5: From geometry to growth -->
    <section class="fractal-text">
      <div class="text-content">
        <p>And then there are fractals that grow with you. The nautilus adds a new chamber to its shell as it grows - each one slightly larger than the last, following a logarithmic spiral.</p>
        <p class="faded">The golden ratio, made habitable.</p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Viz 5: Nautilus -->
    <section class="fractal-section" data-viz="nautilus">
      <canvas></canvas>
      <div class="fractal-info">
        <h2>Nautilus</h2>
        <p>A logarithmic spiral where each chamber is roughly 1.618 times larger than the last. The animal builds its home by following one rule - grow, seal, repeat - and a masterpiece of geometry emerges.</p>
        <span class="fractal-interact">hover to reveal the chambers</span>
      </div>
    </section>

  </div>

  <!-- Side dot navigation -->
  <nav class="fractal-dots" aria-label="Sections">
    <button class="dot active" data-section="0" aria-label="Fern"></button>
    <button class="dot" data-section="1" aria-label="Romanesco"></button>
    <button class="dot" data-section="2" aria-label="Lightning"></button>
    <button class="dot" data-section="3" aria-label="Koch"></button>
    <button class="dot" data-section="4" aria-label="Nautilus"></button>
  </nav>

</Base>

<script>
  import { BarnsleyFern } from '../scripts/lab/barnsley-fern';
  import { RomanescoNatural } from '../scripts/lab/romanesco-natural';
  import { LightningFractal } from '../scripts/lab/lightning-fractal';
  import { KochSnowflake } from '../scripts/lab/koch-snowflake';
  import { NautilusSpiral } from '../scripts/lab/nautilus-spiral';
  import type { BaseVisualization } from '../scripts/lab/base-visualization';

  const sections = document.querySelectorAll('.fractal-section');
  const dots = document.querySelectorAll('.fractal-dots .dot');
  const vizMap = new Map<Element, BaseVisualization>();
  let activeViz: BaseVisualization | null = null;

  const constructors: Record<string, new (canvas: HTMLCanvasElement) => BaseVisualization> = {
    'fern': BarnsleyFern,
    'romanesco': RomanescoNatural,
    'lightning': LightningFractal,
    'koch': KochSnowflake,
    'nautilus': NautilusSpiral,
  };

  const container = document.querySelector('.fractal-container');

  const observer = new IntersectionObserver((entries) => {
    for (const entry of entries) {
      const section = entry.target;
      const idx = Array.from(sections).indexOf(section);

      if (entry.isIntersecting && entry.intersectionRatio > 0.3) {
        let viz = vizMap.get(section);
        if (!viz) {
          const canvas = section.querySelector('canvas')!;
          const type = section.getAttribute('data-viz')!;
          const Ctor = constructors[type];
          if (Ctor) {
            viz = new Ctor(canvas);
            vizMap.set(section, viz);
          }
        }
        if (viz && viz !== activeViz) {
          activeViz?.stop();
          viz.start();
          activeViz = viz;
        }
        dots.forEach((d, i) => d.classList.toggle('active', i === idx));
      }
    }
  }, { threshold: 0.3, root: container });

  sections.forEach(s => observer.observe(s));

  // Dot navigation
  dots.forEach(dot => {
    dot.addEventListener('click', () => {
      const idx = parseInt(dot.getAttribute('data-section') || '0');
      sections[idx]?.scrollIntoView({ behavior: 'smooth' });
    });
  });
</script>

<style is:global>
  /* Dark theme override for fractals page */
  body:has(.fractal-container) {
    background: #1a1a1a;
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .site-header {
    background: #1a1a1a;
    border-bottom-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.06);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .logo {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .nav-links a {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .nav-links a:hover {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .lang-toggle {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4) !important;
    border-color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) .mobile-menu-btn span {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
  }

  body:has(.fractal-container) footer {
    display: none;
  }
</style>

<style>
  .fractal-container {
    scroll-snap-type: y proximity;
    overflow-y: auto;
    height: calc(100vh - 60px);
  }

  /* Visualization sections */
  .fractal-section {
    position: relative;
    width: 100%;
    height: calc(100vh - 60px);
    overflow: hidden;
    scroll-snap-align: start;
  }

  .fractal-section canvas {
    position: absolute;
    inset: 0;
    width: 100%;
    height: 100%;
    display: block;
  }

  .fractal-info {
    position: absolute;
    bottom: 2rem;
    left: 2rem;
    max-width: 380px;
    pointer-events: none;
  }

  .fractal-info h2 {
    font-family: var(--serif, 'EB Garamond', serif);
    font-size: 1.3rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.6);
    margin-bottom: 0.6rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .fractal-info p {
    font-family: var(--serif, 'EB Garamond', serif);
    font-size: 0.85rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
    margin-bottom: 0.5rem;
  }

  .fractal-interact {
    font-family: var(--sans, 'Inter', sans-serif);
    font-size: 0.68rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.08em;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Narrative text sections */
  .fractal-text {
    height: calc(100vh - 60px);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    scroll-snap-align: start;
    position: relative;
  }

  .text-content {
    max-width: 520px;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .text-content p {
    font-family: var(--serif, 'EB Garamond', serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.45);
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .text-content p.faded {
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.25);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  /* Dot navigation */
  .fractal-dots {
    position: fixed;
    right: 1.5rem;
    top: 50%;
    transform: translateY(-50%);
    z-index: 10;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 12px;
  }

  .fractal-dots .dot {
    width: 8px;
    height: 8px;
    border-radius: 50%;
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.2);
    border: none;
    cursor: pointer;
    padding: 0;
    transition: all 0.3s ease;
  }

  .fractal-dots .dot:hover {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.5);
  }

  .fractal-dots .dot.active {
    background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
    transform: scale(1.4);
  }

  /* Intro section */
  .fractal-intro {
    height: calc(100vh - 60px);
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    scroll-snap-align: start;
    position: relative;
  }

  .intro-content {
    max-width: 560px;
    padding: 2rem;
    text-align: center;
  }

  .intro-content h1 {
    font-family: var(--serif, 'EB Garamond', serif);
    font-size: 3.5rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.85);
    margin-bottom: 2.5rem;
    letter-spacing: 0.02em;
  }

  .intro-text {
    font-family: var(--serif, 'EB Garamond', serif);
    font-size: 1.05rem;
    line-height: 1.75;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.4);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-bottom: 1.5rem;
  }

  .scroll-hint {
    margin-top: 3rem;
    color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.15);
    font-size: 1.2rem;
    animation: hint-bounce 2.5s ease-in-out infinite;
  }

  @keyframes hint-bounce {
    0%, 100% { transform: translateY(0); opacity: 0.3; }
    50% { transform: translateY(6px); opacity: 0.6; }
  }

  @media (max-width: 768px) {
    .fractal-container {
      scroll-snap-type: none;
    }

    .fractal-dots {
      right: 0.8rem;
      gap: 8px;
    }

    .fractal-dots .dot {
      width: 6px;
      height: 6px;
    }

    .fractal-info {
      bottom: 1.5rem;
      left: 1.5rem;
      max-width: 280px;
    }

    .fractal-info h2 {
      font-size: 1.1rem;
    }

    .fractal-info p {
      font-size: 0.78rem;
    }

    .intro-content h1 {
      font-size: 2.5rem;
    }

    .text-content {
      padding: 1.5rem;
    }

    .text-content p {
      font-size: 0.95rem;
    }
  }
</style>
